annotationA: Serine hydroxymethyltransferase; Interconversion of serine and glycine; Belongs to the SHMT family
annotationB: Glycine cleavage system H protein, mitochondrial; The glycine cleavage system catalyzes the degradation of glycine. The H protein shuttles the methylamine group of glycine from the P protein to the T protein (By similarity); Belongs to the GcvH family
